comments:
Renamed 1.2.1996 to become the parish of Alrewas & Fradley. See 
    also Table 2, note (u).

Created 1.2.1996 by renaming the parish of Alrewas. See also Table 
    2, note (u).
Abolished 25.3.1884 and added to the parish of Alrewas.

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Rugeley. Abolished 
    1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Rugeley, Brindley Heath, Cannock, 
    Brewood and Armitage with Handsacre. See also Table 2, note (f).

Created 1.4.1934 out of the parish of Brereton. See also Table 
    2, note (r).

Created 1.4.1929 out of the parish of Burntwood Edial & Woodhouses. 
    See also Table 2, note (u).

Abolished 1.4.1929 and divided between the parishes of Burntwood 
    and Farewell & Chorley.

That part which untill 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of 
    Brereton. See also Table 2, note (f).
Abolished 25.3.1884 and added to the parish of Alrewas.
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Swinfen & Packington.

Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Whittington 
    and Streethay.
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Harlaston.
Abolished 1.4.1922 and added to the parish of King's Bromley.

Unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parishes of St. 
    Chad, St. Michael and The Close. Abolished 1.4.1980 and divided between the parishes of Lichfield, Swinfen & Packington and Whittington.

Created 1.4.1980 out of the Lichfield unparished area  and 
    parts of the 
    parishes of Burntwood, Streethay, Swinfen & Packington and Wall. See also Table 
    2, note (u).

Created 1.4.1896 out of the rural part of the parish of Ogley 
    Hay. Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Hammerwich.
Abolished 25.3.1884 and added to the parish of Alrewas.
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Mavesyn Ridware.

Abolished 1894 and divided between the parishes of Wall and St. 
    Michael.

Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Cannock Chase unparished area. See also Table 
    2, note (r).

Created 1894 out of the part of the parish of Shenstone in Brownhills 
    Urban District. See also Table 2, note (f).
Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Lichfield unparished area.
Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Lichfield unparished area.

That part which untill 1.4.1931 formed part of the parish of Shenstone. See 
    also Table 2, note (d).
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Fisherwick.

Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an unparished area. See also Table 
    2, notes (i), (k) and (l).

Unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parish of Tamworth. See also Table 2, note 
    (u).
Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Lichfield unparished area.
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of St. Michael.

Renamed 1.9.1993 to create the parish of Wigginton & Hopwas. 
    See also Table 2, note (i).

Created 1.9.1993 by renaming the parish of Wiggington. See also 
    Table 2, note (u).
